T*
() Tj
T*
([1.1] Plain-text formats are decoded directly from their bytes, while PDF documents are parsed with Apache Tika.) Tj
T*
([1.2] Virtual folders are expressed as slashes in the blob name, and recursion can be enabled per configured source.) Tj
T*
([1.3] An optional extension allowlist restricts which blobs in a folder listing are turned into documents.) Tj
T*
([1.4] Unsupported binaries such as images and Microsoft Office documents are skipped during folder loads.) Tj
T*
([1.5] When a blob is named explicitly, a deliberately unsupported type is reported as an error instead of skipped.) Tj
T*
([1.6] Listing follows the NextMarker pagination cursor so that large containers are fully enumerated.) Tj
T*
([1.7] Each returned document carries metadata: the file name, MIME type, size, and any available timestamps.) Tj
T*
([1.8] This fixture exists to exercise the loader end to end against a real storage account.) Tj
T*
([1.9] It contains several paragraphs so that extraction has meaningful content to return and assert on.) Tj
T*
([1.10] Text extraction should preserve the readable words on every page of a multi-page document.) Tj
T*
([1.11] The loader treats a path with a trailing slash as a folder prefix rather than an exact blob name.) Tj
ET
endstream
